text: At the start of this season, whether it's the men's or the women's team, our goal is to challenge for promotions. And in the first two years of running the men's team, we've won the league. And when we took over the women's team last season, we wanted the same for them. And I applied the exact, the exact same theory. The theory I have is that I think a promotion is about 65, 70% your playing budget to recruit the players who can win you a league. But 20, 25% is the manager as well. You've got to have a manager who knows how to use that budget and create a winning mentality. And that's about 5% luck. And so we approach the exact same methodology that we use to win the league with the men's side. We put out a budget that allows us to attract the right players and we attracted a manager who's got experience of winning at that level. And we did our best to avoid relying on the 5% luck.
